# .gitignore for The Companion (public student bundle)
#
# student-notes-private/ holds personal content the Companion writes for each student
# locally — project plans, notes, references they collect, session handoffs,
# instructor questions. None of that belongs in the public repo. The folder
# scaffolding (README + .gitkeep files) IS tracked so the structure ships
# with the bundle.

# Ignore everything inside student-notes-private/ by default
student-notes-private/**

# Keep the scaffolding so the folder structure ships
!student-notes-private/README.md
!student-notes-private/notes/
!student-notes-private/notes/.gitkeep
!student-notes-private/projects/
!student-notes-private/projects/.gitkeep
!student-notes-private/references/
!student-notes-private/references/.gitkeep

# gaps/ is intentionally NOT ignored. Each student's gap log (gaps/<username>.md)
# is tracked, committed to the student's own fork, and collected by the
# instructor. student-notes-private/ stays local; the gap log is the outbound channel.
